\par 
\tab Rationale: A cluster of air nodes lift an object into the air and support it.\par 
\tab Magick Effects: A series of air nodes is created which levitate one or more objects above the Inscription and hold them in place. The invoker may request that the 
objects be tilted, turned, or moved within the area of effect. This Inscription must therefore be inscribed on a floor, tabletop, or similar surface. Any number of objects may be affected by a single invocation, and the invoker may place objects in, or rem
ove them from, the area of effect at will. There is no weight limit on the objects, only volume.\par 
\tab Any inanimate object or living creature may be lifted with this spell; living beings may resist with WP if so desired.  Affected objects can only be lifted 10
 feet, given clearance. Note that inscriptions designed to hold large objects for long periods of time can take up entire floors!\par 
