\par 
\tab Rationale: The caster\rquote s spirit fortifies those spirits within range, and establishes aethyrial link between the subjects allowing them to support each other.\par 
\tab Magick Effects: All creatures friendly to the caster within the area of effect at the time of 
casting are able to make themselves stay in combat. The creatures affected by the casting must remain together as a group, or the links between them end, ending the spell effect as well.\par 
\tab 
While the spell is in effect, the subject creatures cannot be forced by others to retreat from or leave combat due to wounds, nervousness, psychological disorders, psychological effects such as the fear inspired by undead, etc., nor can they be made to av
oid an imminent combat. Spells or prayers specifically aimed at insti
lling Fear or otherwise breaking ranks are resisted at a +25 bonus. If one of the subjects is forced to leave the area of effect this way, the spell effect ends for him, and the others must each test vs. Leadership or \ldblquote lose confidence\rdblquote 
 and are no longer aided by the spell. (That is, the subjects may not break up voluntarily and maintain the spell\rquote s effect, but can recover if one of their number is forced to flee.)\par 
