\tab 
This thaumaturgic form erects a structure of void energies into which a caster places magickal effects. The magickal effects are then held in the energy matrix until a being with a spirit attempts to cross the perimeter of the area of effect, which matche
s the Inscription itself.  The effect is this similar to a Circle, but is meant to keep beings in rather than out; anything inside the Cage is prevented from leaving until all spells stored in it are exhausted.\par 
\tab 
Cages may be inscribed with the same spells and rituals which may be used in Circles (indicated by the symbol following the spell or ritual title). The caster may charge the cage with such spells and rituals as he knows, and the cage will retain the spell
 effects, discharging them only when a being enters the cage\rquote s area of effect.\par 
\tab The cage\rquote s duration may be extended 24 hours per each extra 4 MP cast into the form when it is activated.\par 
\tab Not all spell and ritual effects can be stored in a thaumaturgic cage. See the list of permitted spells and rituals in \ldblquote Spell Commentaries\rdblquote 
 below. (See Chapter 6: Forms and Summonings, page ??, for a detailed discussion of the thaumaturgic cage.)\par 
